            "votes_up": 6,
            "weighted_score": 0.568876326084137,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Better than any other car x technologies game by a LONG SHOT. Best physics, Best car list, kino mod integration and mod support. It also has great performance unlike car x drift racing online 2."
        },
        {
            "review_id": "227345598",
            "steam_id": "76561199388072108",
            "playtime_minutes": 640,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.523809552192688,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "good performace, can get consistent 144 fps on low settings even in full lobbies.\r\nlearning curve, but very fun when you get to learn tracks. you can play dlc's for free if you join lobbies with people using the dlc map.\r\nthe workshop liveries and maps.\r\ngreat game"
        },
        {
            "review_id": "227186814",
            "steam_id": "76561198737295446",
            "playtime_minutes": 12609,
            "voted_up": true,
            "votes_up": 1,
            "weighted_score": 0.523809552192688,
            "steam_purchase": true,
            "review_text": "Out of every CarX that has released this still continues to be the best. There are tons of vehicle modifications in the base game and if you mod the game with Kino the options are almost endless. I have over 1200 hours on PS5 and when i switched to PC with mods it is like it became an entirely different game. This game should be the standard with any racing game when it comes to vehicle modification."
        },
        {
